The paper deals with stochastic optimization problems, which are commonly studied in the machine learning community. Therefore, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses parallel computing and distributed systems, which suggests that it could be relevant to cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing). The paper also mentions multi-agent systems, which could be related to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Additionally, the paper proposes a new optimization framework, which could be relevant to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.MA (Multiagent Systems).
